25/11/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Dragan Covic, of the BiH tripartite presidency, delivered a Bairam message to all Muslims on Monday (24 November), wishing them peace and plenty. The message, sent on the behalf of the presidency, reiterates the will of the country to develop into a modern state respecting the principles of religious tolerance.
In other news, the BiH Council of Ministers decided Monday to establish an expert panel on international peacekeeping missions. The team will include representatives from the ministries of foreign affairs, security and justice, treasury and finance, as well as the two entities' defence ministries. (SRNA, BBC, Onasa - 24/11/03)
